<DESCRIPT>  ARTS; ENTERTAINMENT  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  AN EXHIBIT covering a century of quilts and sewing tools is open at the
American Museum of Quilts and Textiles, 766 S. Second St., San Jose. The show
includes items on loan from the McHenry Museum of Arts &amp; History in Modesto as
well as works by nationally known artists such as Yvonne Porcella. A reception
will be held July 13 from 1 to 3 p.m., and the exhibit is open from 10 a.m. to
4 p.m. Tuesdays through Saturdays through Aug. 3. Admission is free.
Information: (408) 971-0323.; OPERA OVERTURES: The 21st annual Fall Fashion
Luncheon for the Pacific Presbyterian Hospital Auxiliary begins at 11 a.m.
July 22 at the St. Francis Hotel, Union Square, San Francisco. The show
features opera and symphony evening gowns from Saks Fifth Avenue, which is
hosting a champagne reception at the store afterward. Tickets are $60 and $70.
Information and reservations: (415) 923-3403.  </LEADPARA>
